Assesment 2

Genshin Impact is a rpg game released and developed by MiHoYo Inc. in September 2020. It is a free to play game with in built payment options. By October 2021, Genshin Impact grossed over 2 billion dollars worldwide.The game received highly positive reviews and had 4.7 on Google play store. However, recent anniversary events were not well received by the game users. Google play store rating fell from 4.7 stars to 1.9 stars, which showcases public disappointment with the latest updates and anniversary events. In this research, twitter platform will be used to analyse users responses and potentially launch new marketing campaign to improve game ratings.

Topic modeling and visualization

  1. Preprocess text from your dataset to tidy text and convert it to DocumentTermMatrix
tweet<-
  final_data%>%
  mutate(
    timestamp=ymd_hms(created_at),
    day_of_week=wday(timestamp),
    id=as_factor(row_number())
  )

remove_reg <- "&amp;|&lt;|&gt;|\\d+\\w*\\d*|#\\w+|[^\x01-\x7F]|[[:punct:]]|https\\S*"

tidy_tweets <- tweet %>% 
  filter(!str_detect(text, "^RT")) %>%
  mutate(text = str_remove_all(text, remove_reg)) 

tidy_tweets<-tidy_tweets%>%
  unnest_tokens(word, text, token = "tweets") 
## Using `to_lower = TRUE` with `token = 'tweets'` may not preserve URLs.
tidy_tweets<-tidy_tweets%>%
  filter(
    str_detect(word, "[a-z]")
    )%>%
  anti_join((stop_words))
## Joining, by = "word"
tidy_tweets <- tidy_tweets %>%
  filter(word != "genshin",
         word != "impact",
         word != "im")

bing<-get_sentiments("bing")
nrc<-get_sentiments("nrc")

selected_tweets_tidy<-tidy_tweets%>%select(timestamp, day_of_week, location, word, user_id)

selected_tweets_tidy<-selected_tweets_tidy%>%
  inner_join(bing)%>%
  rename(sentiment_bing=sentiment)%>%
inner_join(nrc)%>%
  rename(sentiment_nrc=sentiment)
## Joining, by = "word"
## Joining, by = "word"
tweets_dtm<-tidy_tweets%>%
  count(id, word)%>%
  cast_dtm(
    document=id,
    term=word,
    value=n,
    weighting=tm::weightTf
    )

  1. Use LDA() function to create an LDA model. Experiment with different number of topics (k=). Visualise the top 10 words from each topic to brainstorm on possible topics that they cover.
tweets_dtm_trim<-tm::removeSparseTerms(tweets_dtm, sparse=.99)
rowTotals <- apply(tweets_dtm_trim, 1, sum)
tweets_dtm_trim <- tweets_dtm_trim[rowTotals> 0, ] 

#LDA for 5 topics
tweets_lda<-LDA(tweets_dtm_trim, k=2, control=list(seed=1234))

tweet_topics<-tidy(tweets_lda, matrix="beta")

#let's look at them with 10 top words for each topic
tweet_top_terms <- tweet_topics %>%
  group_by(topic) %>%
  top_n(10, beta) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  arrange(topic, -beta)

tweet_top_terms %>%
  filter(term != "genshin") %>%
  mutate(term = reorder_within(term, beta, topic)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(term, beta, fill = factor(topic))) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~ topic, scales = "free") +
  coord_flip() +
  scale_x_reordered()

2 topics describe the current users response the best. Topics 2 can be described as positive response on the new event in the game, where the new character “Hu Tao” is introduced. Users use words like love and luck. MiHoYo should closely analyse the response of game users to make sure that company understands what kind of features customers are unsatisfied with. With understanding that latest event was a sucess, company can learn how to better plan and design events in the future.
